<div class="row g-4">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="encoder-panel rounded">
            <h6 class="fw-bold mb-3"><i class="fas fa-user-lock me-2 text-primary"></i>Control Panel Login</h6>

            <div class="form-check form-switch mb-3">
                <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="authEnabled">
                <label class="form-check-label" for="authEnabled">Require sign-in to access control panel</label>
                <div class="form-text ms-4" id="authEnabledHint"></div>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-3">
                <label for="authUsername" class="form-label">Username</label>
                <input type="text" class="form-control" id="authUsername" autocomplete="off">
            </div>

            <div class="mb-3">
                <label for="authPassword" class="form-label">Password</label>
                <input type="password" class="form-control" id="authPassword" placeholder="Leave blank to keep current" autocomplete="new-password">
                <div class="form-text">Stored as a PBKDF2 hash; never displayed back.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="d-flex gap-2 align-items-center">
                <button class="btn btn-primary" id="saveAuthConfig"><i class="fas fa-save me-1"></i>Save</button>
                <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary" id="signOutBtn" type="button"><i class="fas fa-sign-out-alt me-1"></i>Sign out</button>
                <span class="small text-success ms-2" id="authSaveStatus" style="display:none;"><i class="fas fa-check me-1"></i>Saved</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="encoder-panel rounded">
            <h6 class="fw-bold mb-3"><i class="fas fa-shield-alt me-2 text-warning"></i>Notes</h6>
            <ul class="small text-muted mb-0">
                <li>When enabled, every browser request must present a valid session cookie.</li>
                <li>Cluster traffic between master and nodes uses the shared secret configured in the Cluster tab — it is independent of this login.</li>
                <li>Disabling auth rotates the session secret, invalidating all existing cookies.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-12">
        <div class="encoder-panel rounded">
            <h6 class="fw-bold mb-3"><i class="fas fa-key me-2 text-info"></i>API Key — Homarr &amp; other external dashboards</h6>

            <p class="small text-muted">
                Generate an API key to let external dashboards (Homarr, Glance, Dashy, etc.) read Snacks's status via the
                read-only <code>/api/v1/*</code> endpoints. Present it as either an <code>X-Api-Key</code> header or a
                <code>?apiKey=</code> query string — Sonarr/Radarr-compatible. The key is only shown once at generation;
                generate a new one to rotate.
            </p>

            <div class="mb-3" id="apiKeyDisplayRow" style="display:none;">
                <label for="apiKeyValue" class="form-label">Your new API key</label>
                <div class="input-group">
                    <input type="text" class="form-control font-monospace" id="apiKeyValue" readonly>
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary" type="button" id="copyApiKeyBtn">
                        <i class="fas fa-copy me-1"></i>Copy
                    </button>
                </div>
                <div class="form-text text-warning">
                    <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle me-1"></i>
                    Copy this now — it cannot be displayed again. Generate a new key to rotate.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="d-flex gap-2 align-items-center">
                <button class="btn btn-primary" id="generateApiKeyBtn" type="button">
                    <i class="fas fa-key me-1"></i><span id="generateApiKeyBtnLabel">Generate API key</span>
                </button>
                <button class="btn btn-outline-danger" id="revokeApiKeyBtn" type="button" style="display:none;">
                    <i class="fas fa-trash me-1"></i>Revoke
                </button>
                <span class="small text-muted ms-2" id="apiKeyStatus"></span>
            </div>

            <div class="form-text mt-2">
                The key only matters while sign-in is enabled above. With sign-in disabled, the public API is open to
                anyone who can reach this server.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
